originalText.text: Terrible experience.  I had prepaid for parking including an extra $15 for oversize car because i didn't want the hassle of driving around to find a spot.  I had an event to attend and drove in from Long Island - when i got to the garage i was waived off by an extremely rude attendant who told me i could not park.  I told him I had a prepaid voucher- he said he didn't care - call the company.  After driving around and checking with 4 other garages who would not or could not accommodate my car - i ended up missing the event and driving home.

originalText.text:
Horrible experience. I was desperately late for a meeting and stuck looking for parking so I took my chances with this garage. I told the attendant that I would be back at 2:05 and asked him to confirm that I would be charged for one hour. He said yes. I came back to retrieve the car and a different attendant charged double. Little did I know that I had checked in at 12:59, thus going exactly one minute over their grace period.

I paid $47 for 66 minutes of parking.

I had had a stressful morning and upon receiving the emotionless, almost sadistic attitude I broke down in tears. I felt utterly betrayed by the good faith promise that I had gotten from the former attendant.

The attendant I spoke to treated me like I was a nuisance.

When I did not leave right away, because I was trying to catch my breath and calm myself before driving, I was threatened with another charge. I regret that I did not remind him that he had charged me for 2 hours, and I could sat in his lot crying for another 50 minutes.

Truly ruined my day! Park elsewhere and avoid garages entirely if you can!
